# Implementation Plan - Frontend UI Performance Optimization

This plan outlines the optimization strategy to achieve maximum front-end rendering performance, instantaneous tab transitions, and ultra-fast modal opening speeds across the entire React application.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The optimization uses a high-performance HOC wrapper (`withRouterFreezer`) to isolate pages from the React Router context. This guarantees that inactive hidden tabs do not re-render when switching tabs, preventing the "render storm" that currently causes transitions to stutter.

> [!TIP]
> All exit transitions for `Framer Motion` inside `CustomModal` are fully preserved because the outer modal wrapper remains mounted while the inner content is lazy-loaded/unmounted safely.

## Proposed Changes

### Core Architecture & UI Components

#### [NEW] [RouterFreezer.tsx](file:///e:/GIAO_DATA_GOOGLESHEETS/src/components/RouterFreezer.tsx)
- Create a Higher-Order Component (HOC) called `withRouterFreezer` that wraps pages and freezes their React Router context subscriptions when they are not active.
- It tracks `useLocation` and `useSearchParams` in the wrapper. If the page is active, it caches the current params in a ref. If inactive, it passes the cached (frozen) params to the wrapped component, preventing re-renders.

```tsx
import React, { useRef } from 'react';
import { useSearchParams, useLocation } from 'react-router-dom';

export function withRouterFreezer<P extends object>(
  WrappedComponent: React.ComponentType<P & { isActive: boolean; searchParams: URLSearchParams; setSearchParams: any; location: any }>
) {
  const MemoizedInner = React.memo(WrappedComponent) as any;

  return function RouterFreezerWrapper(props: P & { pathToCheck?: string | ((path: string) => boolean) }) {
    const location = useLocation();
    const [searchParams, setSearchParams] = useSearchParams();
    const pathname = location.pathname;
    
    // Check if the current route matches the component path
    const isActive = props.pathToCheck
      ? (typeof props.pathToCheck === 'function' ? props.pathToCheck(pathname) : pathname === props.pathToCheck)
      : true;

    const lastParams = useRef({ searchParams, location });
    if (isActive) {
      lastParams.current = { searchParams, location };
    }

    return (
      <MemoizedInner
        {...props}
        isActive={isActive}
        searchParams={lastParams.current.searchParams}
        setSearchParams={setSearchParams}
        location={lastParams.current.location}
      />
    );
  };
}
```

