### Pages & Tab Components (Applying Freezer and Lazy Modals)

We will refactor the major monolithic pages to use the `withRouterFreezer` HOC, split heavy lists, and implement lazy evaluation for all closed modals.

#### [MODIFY] [Gatekeeper.tsx](file:///e:/GIAO_DATA_GOOGLESHEETS/src/pages/Gatekeeper.tsx)
- Extract the main code body of `Gatekeeper` into `GatekeeperInner`, wrapped with `React.memo`.
- Export `Gatekeeper = withRouterFreezer(GatekeeperInner)` mapping the route to `/gatekeeper`.
- Wrap the children of all 7+ `CustomModal` elements in `{isOpen && ( ... )}` blocks (e.g., `isSettingsModalOpen`, `showDupCheckModal`, etc.) so closed modals do not compile/evaluate JSX.
- Memoize the main queue table and the details section using `useMemo` to isolate rendering when modal toggles or hover state changes.

